2026-06-16 09:02:25,631 DEBUG response: Here are three options focused on the dynamic routing work, since the UI tweaks don't add much to the narrative:

- Stopped manually duplicating page files for every new project. Switched to slug-based routing and finally treated content as data instead of hardcoded templates.
- Realized a site isn't an app until it stops relying on copy-pasted pages. Built dynamic routing so the URL actually drives the layout and assets.
- Hardcoding routes works until the maintenance tax becomes real. Added dynamic routing to pull project metadata and images from slugs. Finally feels like actual infrastructure.
